            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-25639",
              "name": "LanguageSpecificPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "axios: Axios affected by Denial of Service via __proto__ Key in mergeConfig"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Axios is a promise based HTTP client for the browser and Node.js. Prior to versions 0.30.3 and 1.13.5, the mergeConfig function in axios crashes with a TypeError when processing configuration objects containing __proto__ as an own property. An attacker can trigger this by providing a malicious configuration object created via JSON.parse(), causing complete denial of service. This vulnerability is fixed in versions 0.30.3 and 1.13.5."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-25639",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-25639\nSeverity: HIGH\nPackage: axios\nFixed Version: 1.13.5, 0.30.3\nLink: [CVE-2026-25639](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-25639)\nAxios is a promise based HTTP client for the browser and Node.js. Prior to versions 0.30.3 and 1.13.5, the mergeConfig function in axios crashes with a TypeError when processing configuration objects containing __proto__ as an own property. An attacker can trigger this by providing a malicious configuration object created via JSON.parse(), causing complete denial of service. This vulnerability is fixed in versions 0.30.3 and 1.13.5.",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-25639**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|HIGH|axios|1.13.5, 0.30.3|[CVE-2026-25639](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-25639)|\n\nAxios is a promise based HTTP client for the browser and Node.js. Prior to versions 0.30.3 and 1.13.5, the mergeConfig function in axios crashes with a TypeError when processing configuration objects containing __proto__ as an own property. An attacker can trigger this by providing a malicious configuration object created via JSON.parse(), causing complete denial of service. This vulnerability is fixed in versions 0.30.3 and 1.13.5."
              },
